28:39.340 --> 28:41.200
BLANCA: Realness is what it's all about.

28:41.260 --> 28:43.330
Being able to fit into the
straight, white world,

28:43.340 --> 28:45.400
to embody the American dream.

28:46.110 --> 28:48.370
But we don't have access to that dream.

28:48.470 --> 28:50.840
And it's not because
of ability. Trust me.

28:50.910 --> 28:52.839
PRAY TELL: We're calling this executive

28:52.840 --> 28:55.140
hustler realness, y'all.

28:55.280 --> 28:58.180
The sepia Don Corleone.

28:58.280 --> 28:59.720
At the Russian Tea Room.

28:59.820 --> 29:01.700
I mean, isn't that what
you're trying to do?

29:01.760 --> 29:03.490
Dance your way into that world?

29:03.590 --> 29:05.560
The world of acceptability?

29:05.660 --> 29:07.560
PRAY TELL: Don't scare the white people!

29:07.660 --> 29:09.560
Don't scare the white folks, y'all!

29:09.660 --> 29:11.500
[WHOOPS]

29:11.600 --> 29:13.630
DAMON: I'm sorry I said
I wasn't like you.

29:13.730 --> 29:15.240
Oh, child, hush.

29:15.460 --> 29:17.480
You are a gay, black boy.

29:17.520 --> 29:19.740
Who else you gonna find
to make you feel superior?

29:21.240 --> 29:22.580
Can I get you more coffee, ma'am?

29:22.640 --> 29:25.120
Um, no, thank you, sweetie.
I'll be up all night.

29:25.160 --> 29:26.240
Sure. You okay?

29:29.120 --> 29:30.950
[LAUGHS]

29:31.050 --> 29:32.850
Okay.

29:32.950 --> 29:36.050
So, do you have, like, a real job or...

29:36.160 --> 29:38.720
I don't judge people
based on how they live.

29:38.830 --> 29:41.280
I'm lucky I can mostly pass.

29:42.260 --> 29:43.730
<i>I've taken the hormones.</i>

29:43.830 --> 29:46.000
<i>I know how to carry myself.</i>

29:47.970 --> 29:51.960
I kept who I was quiet from
my parents for a long time.

29:52.840 --> 29:54.740
I would wait until they went to sleep,

29:54.840 --> 29:58.379
